author: William Hughes
title: Newswire: Lady Gaga to grace RuPaul’s Drag Race with her royal presence
text:
Share Tweet 
In a move that would likely send the Alex Jones fans of the world into a frothing, devil-hunting horde—if the existence of Logo and its brand of LGBTQ-inclusive programming didn’t have them permanently there already—the producers of RuPaul’s Drag Race have announced that recent Super Bowl star and “goddess of Satan” herself, Lady Gaga, will appear on the show’s upcoming season premiere. 
According to a press release sent out by the show, Gaga will serve as a guest judge on the episode, helping RuPaul pass judgment on season 9’s new crop of fiercely battling queens. You can get a brief taste of her appearance (and judge whether her brand of arch, elaborately dressed camp gels with that of the show) in the teaser video above. 
Season nine of RuPaul’s Drag Race premieres this March.
